In a saucepan, cook the eggs and milk over medium heat for 8 minutes or until a thermometer reads 160 degrees F and mixture coats a metal spoon. Stir in sugar until dissolved. Cool. Stir in the cream and pineapple. Fill cylinder of ice cream freezer two-thirds full; freeze according to manufacturer's directions. Refrigerate remaining mixture until ready to freeze. Allow ice cream to ripen in refrigerator freezer for 2-4 hours before serving. May be frozen for up to 2 months.